<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910506-0154</DOCNO><DOCID>910506-0154.</DOCID><HL>   Harsco Forecast for '91</HL><DATE>05/06/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   HSC</CO><MS>INDUSTRIAL (IDU)</MS><IN>DIVERSIFIED INDUSTRIAL (IDD)</IN><RE>PENNSYLVANIA (PA)</RE><LP>   HARRISBURG, Pa. -- Harsco Corp. Chairman Malcolm W.Gambill said he expects it will be difficult for theindustrial concern to match its 1990 performance because ofweak construction markets and unstable resin prices. In 1990,Harsco earned $72.5 million, or $2.77 a share.   The chief executive, in remarks scheduled to be presentedto the New York Society of Security Analysts today, said henevertheless expects 1991 to be a good year.</LP><TEXT>   In the 1991 first quarter, Harsco earned $12 million, or46 cents a share, down from $13 million, or 50 cents a share,in the 1990 first quarter. Mr. Gambill said, however, thatthe engineered products and defense groups weren't hurt bythe construction slowdown and resin price instability.</TEXT></DOC>